CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 18, 1961, pg. A14 reads: "Gay Time - Enjoying the hospitality of Mr. and Mrs. Gregory Pitts (far right), at the Kappa Karnival, last week, were, counter clockwise: Miss Kathleen Holloway, Louis Walker, Mr. and Mrs. Edward King, Mrs. Lucius Walker, Mrs. James Burwell, Mr. and Mrs. Andrew Turner, Mr. and Mrs. Theodore Baker, Ralph Robinson, Sandra Williamson, Mrs. Kelly Williams and James Burwell, back to camera. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, counterclockwise: Nancy and Gregory Pitts, Kathleen Holloway, Louis Walker, Mr. and Mrs. Edward King, Mrs. Lucius Walker, Mrs. James Burwell, Mr. and Mrs. Andrew Turner, standing; Mr. and Mrs. Theodore Baker, Ralph Robinson, Sandra Williamson, Kelly Williams, and James Burwell, gathered around banquet table in the Anchorage for Kappa Alpha Psi's Kappa Karnival
